Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Excellent parking and on site amenity

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Available for lease is a fitted out office with additional warehousing, located in City Views Estate at 65 Epping Road.
The estate has recently undergone extensive upgrades, to both services and amenity offering.

+ Fitted part office floor, benefiting from a complete fitout, including; reception, multiple breakout areas, board/meeting rooms, open plan and perimeter offices.
+ Basement warehouse with raised dock access and goods lift access from warehouse to office floor.
+ The elevated location enjoys city views, + newly upgraded building lifts and lift lobbies
+ Short walk to Macquarie Park train station
+ On-site childcare and tennis court
+ New end of trip facilities, bike racks and on-site cafe
+ Plenty of parking, being a mix of basement and external
+ Flexible lease term available

For further details please contract exclusive leasing agents CBRE:

Ben Byford 0414 722 935
Peter Mangraviti 0413 750 350

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: MACQUARIE PARK – FITTED OUT OFFICE & WAREHOUSE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
A boutique mixed use office / warehouse building located in Macquarie Park, allowing multi-directional travel given the proximity of the M2, Epping Road and Lane Cove Road.

The accommodation comprises the entire top floor of offices, which has the benefit of a large external breakout balcony, currently fitted out as offices, open plan, large kitchen, shower, meeting rooms and support areas. 

The high clearance warehouse is located at the rear of the property and accessed via a roller shutter door. 

Car parking is configured under the building and externally ongrade. NABERS exempt.

• Warehouse of 626.1sqm
• Office of 618.8sqm
• Up to 35 car spaces

Available May 2019.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Office areas offered with new fit outs

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The property is situated on the Southern side of Wicks Road, providing immediate access to Macquarie Park via Waterloo Road, within a strategic pocket of land broadly bound by Epping Road, Wicks Road and the M2 Motorway. 

+ The building is a short walk from either North Ryde or from the Macquarie Park Metro Station. 
+ Surrounding amenity Lachlan’s Line offers including 2,500sqm Coles Supermarket, Harvey Norman/Domayne store, Officeworks.
+ The building comprises high quality office situated over the top two storeys with balconies spanning the width of the building. The efficient central core conﬁguration enhances the natural light to all levels.
+ Access to all ﬂoors, including the warehousing and basement car parking is accessed via lift or stairs.


The current availability benefits from:
+ Refurbished and fitted out office suites with areas:
157, 350/350 or 712.2sqm
+ Rare High clearance Warehouse with 20ft container access 1,289.7sqm (must be leased with office)

For further details please contact exclusive leasing agents CBRE & Knight Frank.

CBRE are pleased to present 63-65 Waterloo Road to market for lease.

One of the last remaining genuine freestanding office/warehouse facilities in Macquarie Park the property presents are rare opportunity for an occupier to use the facility for office, laboratory, warehousing or educational purposes.

Centrally located on Waterloo Road the property enjoys close proximity to Macquarie Train station and Macquarie Shopping Centre with both being within a short walking distance.

Key features:

+ Stand alone office and warehouse facility
+ Fitted out office space
+ High clearance warehouse
+ High car parking ratio
+ Prime location

For more information or to arrange an inspection, please contact exclusive CBRE agents

Situated at the cul de sac end of Eden Park Drive in one of Macquarie Park's best enclaves, offering excellent amenity in walking distance. Approximately 150 metres* from Macquarie Park Train Station with easy access via Waterloo Road to Epping Road, Lane Cove Road and the M2 Motorway.

Rydecorp is a modern office and warehouse development, consisting of 16 individual units ranging from 420sqm* to 1,100sqm*. The estate has recently undergone a refurbishment.

The available units offers a mix of office and warehouse. The warehouses are high clearance, many are clear span and enjoy undercover loading. The office provides direct ground floor access and the warehouse is discreetly located to the rear of the estate, the warehouse has excellent all weather undercover loading

The estate benefits from:
- Potential to retain existing office fit out
- Ample cafes and staff amenity in Eden Park Drive precinct
- Secure 24/7 swipe card access,
- CCTV throughout all common areas,
- Full control on air conditioning operating hours as each unit has its own ducted air.
- A mix of external undercover and basement car spaces
- New passenger lifts servicing all levels
- Attractive glass curtain facade providing a modern street frontage,
- All units are self-contained with own kitchen and amenities.

For further details or to arrange an inspection, please contact Exclusive Leasing Agents.
